# This scenario provokes an upstream reset on purpose, so the [error] line it
# produces is the EXPECTED outcome, not a finding. Without an exemption the
# per-scenario error-log scrape fails the run on the very line the scenario
# exists to cause.
#
# Scoped to that one message rather than turned off wholesale: a segfault, a
# double-finalize or a slab exhaustion in the same run still fails the scrape,
# which is the whole point of PROBER_ALLOW_LOG being a pattern and not a flag.
# The rule file asserts this same text POSITIVELY via grep_error_log, so the
# two cannot drift -- exempting a line the scenario no longer produces would
# fail the grep.
PROBER_ALLOW_LOG='recv\(\) failed .*while reading response header from upstream'
